<paragraph id="F25736F94F34FF9804B4FBAFFD435237" blockId="25.[172,733,1082,1107]" box="[172,733,1082,1107]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">
(
<figureCitation id="6AD32A7C4F34FF9804ACFBAFFE8E5237" box="[180,272,1082,1107]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[163,244,905,927]" captionTargetBox="[164,1447,197,865]" captionTargetId="figure-453@2.[163,1449,195,866]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figure 1. A, maximum clade credibility tree of the Afrotropical freshwater crab fauna based on four DNA loci with support values (posterior probabilities and bootstrap values of the ML analyses) with a geological timescale below the tree topology. Posterior probabilities&gt; 0.95 pP (*above branch) and bootstrap values&gt; 75% (* below branch) were regarded as statistically supported and are shown on the tree topology. Clade A, Liberonautinae, clade B, Potamonautinae, clade B1, Maritimonautini, clade B2, Erimetopini, clade B3, Potamonautini. B, detail of the maximum clade credibility tree of the Afrotropical freshwater crab fauna showing Clade B3 Potamonautini with the species included in the five genera within the tribe: Arcopotamonautes (B3[1]), Lirrangopotamonautes (B3[2]), Platythelphusa (B3[3]), Potamonautes s.s. (B3[4]) and Rotundopotamonautes (B3[5])." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461481/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">FIGS 1B</figureCitation>
<figureCitation id="6AD32A7C4F34FF980509FBAFFE815237" box="[273,287,1082,1107]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="12.[163,240,1244,1266]" captionTargetBox="[163,1443,195,1204]" captionTargetId="figure-242@12.[163,1443,195,1204]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 3. Gonopods 1 and 2 of four genera in Liberonautinae. A–C, Buea asylos (Cumberlidge et al., 2019: fig. 7a, d; 8a); D–F, Potamonemus mambilorum (Cumberlidge et al., 2019: fig. 7b, e; 8b); G–I, Sudanonautes floweri; J–L, Louisea balssi (Mvogo Ndongo et al., 2018: fig. 5a–c, © Magnolia Press, reproduced with permission from the copyright holder). A, D, G, J, left G1 ventral view; B, E, H, K, left G1 dorsal view; C, F, I, L, left G2 ventral view. Scale bar: A, B, D, E, G, H, J, K = 2.0 mm, C, F, I, L = 1.8 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461485" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461485/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="6AD32A7C4F34FF980535FBAFFEF35237" box="[301,365,1082,1107]" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="15.[145,224,1409,1431]" captionTargetBox="[145,1425,195,1369]" captionTargetId="figure-190@15.[145,1425,195,1369]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Figure 5. Gonopods 1 and 2 of one genus in Maritimonautini and three genera in Potamonautini. A–C, Maritimonautes obesus; D–F, Arcopotamonautes suprasulcatus; G–I, Lirrangopotamonautes dybowskii; J–L, Platythelphusa armata. Scale bar: A, B, G–L = 2.0 mm, C, F = 1.8 mm; D, E = 5.0 mm; L = 6.7 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461489" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461489/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">5D–L</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="6AD32A7C4F34FF980562FBAFFE295237" box="[378,439,1082,1107]" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="16.[163,241,788,810]" captionTargetBox="[164,1443,195,749]" captionTargetId="figure-409@16.[163,1443,195,749]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figure 6. Gonopods 1 and 2 of two genera in Potamonautini. A–C, Potamonautes anchetiae (CAW 450A), Angola. A, D, left G1 ventral view. D–F, Rotundopotamonautes loveni, Kenya, B, E, left G1 dorsal view; C, F, left G2 ventral view. Scale bar: A, B, D, E = 2.0 mm, C, F = 1.8 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461491/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">6A–F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="6AD32A7C4F34FF9805DCFBAFFE7B5237" box="[452,485,1082,1107]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="17.[145,224,1267,1289]" captionTargetBox="[225,1345,195,1227]" captionTargetId="figure-288@17.[225,1345,195,1227]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 8. Maps showing the distributional ranges of (A) Potamonautinae, (B) Maritimonautini, (C) Erimetopini and (D) Potamonautini." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461497/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">8D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="6AD32A7C4F34FF9805EAFBAFFD3A5236" box="[498,676,1082,1107]" captionStart="Figure 10" captionStartId="19.[145,226,1652,1674]" captionTargetBox="[305,1265,197,1611]" captionTargetId="figure-150@19.[305,1265,195,1612]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figure 10. Maps showing the distributional ranges of the five genera of Potamonautini. (A) Arcopotamonautes, (B) Lirrangopotamonautes, (C) Platythelphusa, (D) Potamonautes s.s. and (E) Rotundopotamonautes." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461503" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461503/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">10A–E; TABLES</figureCitation>
1–3)
</paragraph>
