<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F34FF980489F9E7FEBB50E3" box="[145,293,1650,1671]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">Distribution:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F34FF980521F9E7FE7B50EC" baseAuthorityName="Bott" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[313,485,1650,1672]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="1274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Potamonautini">Potamonautini</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed in sub-Saharan Africa in eastern and northern Africa (
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F34FF980481F925FE8C50A2" box="[153,274,1712,1734]" name="Tanzania" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">Tanzania</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F34FF98053CF925FEE950A1" box="[292,375,1712,1733]" name="Kenya" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">Kenya</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F34FF980590F925FDAC50A2" box="[392,562,1712,1734]" name="South Sudan" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">South Sudan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F34FF98065BF925FD0850A2" box="[579,662,1712,1734]" name="Sudan" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">Sudan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F34FF9806BFF925FD6D50A1" box="[679,755,1712,1733]" name="Egypt" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">Egypt</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F34FF980489F95BFF675080" box="[145,249,1742,1764]" name="Somalia" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">Somalia</collectingCountry>
) and southern Africa (
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F34FF98063FF95BFD1D5080" box="[551,643,1742,1764]" name="Angola" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">Angola</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F34FF98068CF95BFD6D5080" box="[660,755,1742,1764]" name="Malawi" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">Malawi</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F34FF980489F978FEBA5167" box="[145,292,1773,1795]" name="Mozambique" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F34FF980537F978FE195167" box="[303,391,1773,1795]" name="Zambia" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">Zambia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F34FF980589F978FD965167" box="[401,520,1773,1795]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F34FF98060BF97BFD1B5167" box="[531,645,1774,1795]" name="Botswana" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">Botswana</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F34FF980688F978FD6B5167" box="[656,757,1773,1795]" name="Namibia" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">Namibia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F34FF980489F899FEB45146" box="[145,298,1804,1826]" name="South Africa" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">South Africa</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F34FF98052FF899FE3F5146" box="[311,417,1804,1826]" name="Swaziland" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">Eswatini</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F34FF9805C7F899FDA35146" box="[479,573,1804,1826]" name="Lesotho" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">Lesotho</collectingCountry>
) (
<figureCitation id="6AD32A7C4F34FF98064EF899FD335145" box="[598,685,1804,1826]" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="17.[145,224,1267,1289]" captionTargetBox="[225,1345,195,1227]" captionTargetId="figure-288@17.[225,1345,195,1227]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 8. Maps showing the distributional ranges of (A) Potamonautinae, (B) Maritimonautini, (C) Erimetopini and (D) Potamonautini." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461497" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461497/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">Fig. 8D</figureCitation>
). This tribe is not found in West Africa (from 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F34FF980660F8BFFD495124" box="[632,727,1834,1856]" name="Senegal" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">Senegal</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="8AFF76694F34FF980489F8DCFF75513B" box="[145,235,1865,1887]" name="Nigeria" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F25736F94F34FF980731FF50FA8C5732" blockId="25.[809,1425,197,342]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F34FF980731FF50FC0A56BE" box="[809,916,197,218]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="35E84D7A4F34FF9807B8FF50FBD456BF" baseAuthorityName="Bott" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[928,1098,197,219]" class="Malacostraca" family="Potamonautidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="25" pageNumber="1274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Potamonautini">Potamonautini</taxonomicName>
includes five genera and 101 species that form a well-supported and highly diverse group in the present study (
<figureCitation id="6AD32A7C4F34FF98007DFE97FB28577C" box="[1125,1206,258,280]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[163,244,905,927]" captionTargetBox="[164,1447,197,865]" captionTargetId="figure-453@2.[163,1449,195,866]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figure 1. A, maximum clade credibility tree of the Afrotropical freshwater crab fauna based on four DNA loci with support values (posterior probabilities and bootstrap values of the ML analyses) with a geological timescale below the tree topology. Posterior probabilities&gt; 0.95 pP (*above branch) and bootstrap values&gt; 75% (* below branch) were regarded as statistically supported and are shown on the tree topology. Clade A, Liberonautinae, clade B, Potamonautinae, clade B1, Maritimonautini, clade B2, Erimetopini, clade B3, Potamonautini. B, detail of the maximum clade credibility tree of the Afrotropical freshwater crab fauna showing Clade B3 Potamonautini with the species included in the five genera within the tribe: Arcopotamonautes (B3[1]), Lirrangopotamonautes (B3[2]), Platythelphusa (B3[3]), Potamonautes s.s. (B3[4]) and Rotundopotamonautes (B3[5])." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461481/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
<figureCitation id="6AD32A7C4F34FF9800AEFE96FB5A577C" box="[1206,1220,259,280]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="12.[163,240,1244,1266]" captionTargetBox="[163,1443,195,1204]" captionTargetId="figure-242@12.[163,1443,195,1204]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Figure 3. Gonopods 1 and 2 of four genera in Liberonautinae. A–C, Buea asylos (Cumberlidge et al., 2019: fig. 7a, d; 8a); D–F, Potamonemus mambilorum (Cumberlidge et al., 2019: fig. 7b, e; 8b); G–I, Sudanonautes floweri; J–L, Louisea balssi (Mvogo Ndongo et al., 2018: fig. 5a–c, © Magnolia Press, reproduced with permission from the copyright holder). A, D, G, J, left G1 ventral view; B, E, H, K, left G1 dorsal view; C, F, I, L, left G2 ventral view. Scale bar: A, B, D, E, G, H, J, K = 2.0 mm, C, F, I, L = 1.8 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6461485" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6461485/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">3</figureCitation>
), as well as in the most recent molecular studies of this fauna (
<bibRefCitation id="96794B084F34FF980107FEB4FC315731" author="Daniels SR &amp; Klaus S" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293" pagination="119 - 128" refId="ref33119" refString="Daniels SR, Klaus S. 2018. Divergent evolutionary origins and biogeographic histories of two freshwater crabs (Brachyura: Potamonautes) on the West African conveyer belt islands of Sao Tome and Principe. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution 127: 119 - 128." type="journal article" year="2018">Daniels &amp; Klaus, 2018</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 1; 
<bibRefCitation id="96794B084F34FF9807E7FED5FB215731" author="Wood LE &amp; De Grave S &amp; Cumberlidge N &amp; Kennerley A &amp; Daniels SR" box="[1023,1215,320,342]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293" pagination="2219 - 2230" refId="ref37030" refString="Wood LE, De Grave S, Cumberlidge N, Kennerley A, Daniels SR. 2019. A phylogenetic perspective on biodiversity patterns of Afrotropical freshwater crabs (Crustacea, Decapoda, Potamonautidae). Aquatic Conservation: Marine and Freshwater Ecosystems 29: 2219 - 2230." type="journal article" year="2019">
Wood 
<emphasis id="C09CEAEB4F34FF98005BFED5FBE55731" box="[1091,1147,320,341]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1293">et al.</emphasis>
, 2019
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 1).
</paragraph>
